definitions: relating to or occurring at the early morning period when the sun appears above the horizon
examples: The sunrise yoga class attracts dedicated practitioners
She captured stunning sunrise photographs at the beach

definitions: of excellent quality, impressive and outstanding in every aspect or detail
examples: The chef prepared a superb meal for the guests
Her performance in the play was absolutely superb

definitions: equipped with a device that increases engine power by forcing extra air into the combustion chamber
filled with intense energy, excitement, or emotion beyond normal levels
examples: The supercharged engine roared to life instantly
He drove a supercharged sports car on weekends
The crowd created a supercharged atmosphere at the concert
Their supercharged emotions made rational discussion impossible

definitions: relating to a substance at temperature and pressure above its critical point where distinct liquid and gas phases do not exist
of the highest importance or severity requiring immediate attention or action
examples: The supercritical fluid extraction process yields pure compounds
Supercritical carbon dioxide is used in decaffeination processes
The reactor reached supercritical conditions requiring emergency shutdown
This supercritical decision will affect the company's future

definitions: existing or occurring at or on the surface rather than penetrating below
not thorough, deep, or complete in understanding, character, or substance
examples: The doctor treated her superficial wounds with antiseptic
Only superficial damage occurred to the car's paint
His superficial knowledge of physics showed during the debate
Their superficial friendship ended when real problems arose

definitions: exceeding what is sufficient or necessary, serving no useful purpose in the current context
examples: The report contained superfluous details that obscured main points
She removed all superfluous decorations from the minimalist design

definitions: having or showing exceptional ability or powers beyond what is normally possible for humans
examples: The rescue required superhuman strength to lift the debris
She displayed superhuman patience with the difficult students

definitions: placed or laid over something else, especially so that both are still evident or visible
examples: The superimposed images created an interesting artistic effect
Subtitles were superimposed on the foreign film scenes

definitions: of the highest quality or degree, surpassing all others in excellence
denoting the form of adjective or adverb expressing the highest degree of quality
examples: The restaurant received superlative reviews from food critics
Her superlative performance earned a standing ovation
'Best' is the superlative form of 'good'
Students practiced using superlative adjectives in sentences

definitions: attributed to forces beyond scientific understanding or the laws of nature, often involving mystical elements
examples: Many cultures have supernatural beliefs about life after death
The movie featured supernatural creatures and unexplained phenomena

definitions: present in excess of the normal, required, or usual number in a particular context or system
examples: The patient had supernumerary teeth requiring dental extraction
Supernumerary staff were hired for the holiday season

definitions: written or printed above and to the side of another character in smaller size
examples: Mathematical exponents are written in superscript format
The footnote reference appeared as a superscript number

definitions: involving or denoting speed greater than that of sound in air at sea level
examples: The supersonic jet broke the sound barrier effortlessly
Supersonic flight creates distinctive shock wave patterns

definitions: having or showing excessive belief in supernatural influences or practices based on fear or ignorance
examples: His superstitious nature prevented him from walking under ladders
The superstitious sailor always carried his lucky charm

definitions: observed and directed by someone in authority to ensure proper completion or behavior
examples: Children must swim in the supervised area only
The supervised training program lasted for six months

definitions: having or relating to the role of watching and directing work or workers
examples: She accepted a supervisory position at the factory
His supervisory duties included reviewing employee performance

definitions: lying face upward on the back with the face and torso facing up
failing to act or protest through weakness or indifference when action is needed
examples: The patient remained in a supine position during examination
Supine exercises help strengthen core muscles effectively
Their supine acceptance of injustice disappointed many supporters
The government's supine response to crisis angered citizens

definitions: bending and moving easily and gracefully with smooth flexibility and without stiffness
examples: Regular yoga practice keeps the body supple and strong
The supple leather jacket molded perfectly to her form

definitions: provided in addition to what already exists to complete or enhance something
examples: Students received supplemental materials for advanced study topics
The company offers supplemental insurance coverage to employees

definitions: completing or enhancing something by providing what is lacking or additional material
examples: The teacher provided supplementary worksheets for extra practice
Supplementary vitamins helped improve her overall health condition

definitions: borne or held up by a structure or foundation to prevent falling
given assistance, encouragement, or approval by others in various forms
examples: The roof is supported by strong steel beams
Her injured leg needs to be supported while walking
The research findings are supported by extensive data
He felt supported by his family during difficult times

definitions: bearing weight or providing assistance to maintain stability or function
playing a secondary but important role that helps the main element succeed
examples: The supporting walls bear the building's structural load
Supporting evidence strengthened the prosecutor's case significantly
She won an award for best supporting actress
The supporting characters added depth to the story

definitions: forcibly put an end to or prevented from being expressed or revealed
consciously inhibited or restrained from natural expression of emotions or desires
examples: The suppressed information was later revealed by whistleblowers
Government forces suppressed the rebellion within days
Her suppressed anger finally erupted during the meeting
Years of suppressed memories surfaced during therapy sessions

definitions: tending to suppress, restrain, or prevent expression, activity, or development of something
examples: The regime's suppressive policies limited freedom of speech
Suppressive fire kept enemy forces from advancing positions

definitions: having power or influence that transcends national boundaries or governments operating above nation-state level
examples: The European Union is a supranational organization
Supranational courts can override national legal decisions

definitions: relating to or used in surgery or operations performed by surgeons
done with extreme precision and accuracy like a surgical procedure
examples: The patient required surgical intervention to remove tumors
Nurses prepared surgical instruments for the operation
The military conducted a surgical strike on enemy positions
Her surgical precision in editing improved the manuscript

definitions: moving suddenly and powerfully forward or upward in a strong wavelike motion
examples: The surging crowd pushed toward the concert stage
Surging waves crashed against the rocky shoreline continuously

definitions: bad-tempered and unfriendly in manner showing hostility or rudeness
examples: The surly waiter barely acknowledged our presence
His surly attitude made collaboration difficult and unpleasant

definitions: having overcome a difficulty or obstacle, or having something placed on top
examples: The monument is surmounted by a golden eagle
They successfully surmounted all obstacles to graduation

definitions: incomparably great or excellent, exceeding or superior to what is common
examples: Her surpassing beauty captivated everyone at the gala
The artist demonstrated surpassing skill in portrait painting

definitions: having the qualities of surrealism marked by bizarre, dreamlike distortion of reality
examples: The accident scene had a surreal quality about it
Walking through the empty city felt completely surreal

definitions: having qualities characteristic of surrealism combining unrelated images in bizarre, dreamlike ways
examples: The film used surrealistic imagery to convey psychological states
Her surrealistic paintings challenged conventional artistic perspectives

definitions: acting as a substitute or replacement for someone or something else
examples: She served as a surrogate mother for the couple
The doll became a surrogate child for her

definitions: relating to Kazakhstan or its people, culture, or language
examples: The Kazakhstani delegation arrived for trade negotiations
She studied Kazakhstani folk music for her thesis

definitions: relating to Kenya or its people, culture, or language
examples: Kenyan runners dominated the marathon competition again
The restaurant serves authentic Kenyan cuisine daily

definitions: relating to the economic theories of John Maynard Keynes advocating government intervention in the economy
examples: The government adopted Keynesian policies during the recession
Keynesian economics emphasizes demand-side solutions to downturns

definitions: relating to the Kurds or their language and culture
examples: She learned to speak Kurdish from her grandmother
The museum featured an exhibition of Kurdish art

definitions: relating to Kuwait or its people, culture, or language
examples: The Kuwaiti embassy hosted a cultural exchange event
Kuwaiti oil reserves are among the world's largest

definitions: relating to Kyrgyzstan or its people, culture, or language
examples: The Kyrgyzstani team competed in the winter Olympics
Traditional Kyrgyzstani yurts dotted the mountain landscape

definitions: having something on all sides creating a complete enclosure or barrier
examples: The castle was surrounded by a deep moat
She felt surrounded by supportive friends and family

definitions: continuing to live or exist despite hardship, danger, or difficult circumstances
remaining in existence when other similar things have been lost or destroyed
examples: The surviving passengers were rescued after three days
Only two surviving members attended the reunion
The museum displays surviving artifacts from ancient civilizations
This is the only surviving copy of the manuscript

definitions: likely or liable to be influenced or harmed by a particular thing
easily affected emotionally or having little resistance to something harmful
examples: Young children are particularly susceptible to peer pressure
The metal is susceptible to rust in humidity
She was susceptible to colds during winter months
His susceptible nature made him believe every story

definitions: believed to be guilty, true, or likely but without certain proof
examples: The suspected thief was questioned by police officers
Doctors ordered tests for the suspected viral infection

definitions: hanging from something above so as to be free on all sides except at the point of support
temporarily prevented from continuing or being in force or effect
examples: Beautiful crystals were suspended from the chandelier
The bridge was suspended high above the river
His driver's license was suspended for six months
The game remained suspended due to heavy rain

definitions: arousing excited anticipation or uncertainty about what will happen creating dramatic tension
examples: The suspenseful movie kept audiences on edge throughout
She writes suspenseful novels that readers can't put down

definitions: continuing for an extended period or without interruption at a consistent level
examples: The economy showed sustained growth over five years
Her sustained effort finally produced the desired results

definitions: having or showing confident, arrogant, or aggressive self-assurance in manner or appearance
examples: His swagger attitude annoyed his more modest colleagues
The team maintained their swagger style throughout the season

definitions: characteristic of or resembling a swamp with soft, wet, spongy ground
examples: The swampy terrain made hiking extremely difficult
Mosquitoes thrived in the swampy conditions near the river

definitions: stylishly luxurious and expensive displaying wealth or sophistication ostentatiously
examples: They stayed at a swank hotel overlooking Central Park
The swank restaurant required formal attire for dinner
